notesStmt.note: This workshop discussion is part of a European student conference on the future of English in Europe. This event is a socratic dialogue between participants of a European student conference on the topic of English as a lingua franca and regional culture. The aim of the socratic dialogue is to ask questions, give answers, and summarize others' statement in order to make sure that one understands what the others said. The discussion revolves around a possible definition of the topic English as a lingua franca. S1 is the chair of the discussion and assigns turns. She is also the one who can ask others to repeat what participants have just said.

namespace.tagUsage: Used to mark a stretch of speech commonly preceded and followed by a pause or by a change of speaker. Auis, however, not required to be bounded by a pause or a change of speaker, nor does it represent a turn in a conversation analytic sense. At a minimum, auis some phonetic production or noise made by a given speaker or a group of speakers.
